  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version:\r\n```\r\n$ ./build/bin/geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.7-unstable\r\nGit Commit: 538f763fdc304329d6231e6cb31efab4cba5153e\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.12.1\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=/home/ia/go\r\nGOROOT=/home/ia/go1.12.1.linux-amd64/go\r\n```\r\nOS & Version: \r\n```\r\n$ uname -a\r\nLinux ubp52 5.2.9-050209-generic #201908160940 SMP Fri Aug 16 09:42:58 UTC 2019 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n`clef` is able to sign a bare-minimum valid transaction using the `account_signTransaction` method.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n`clef` reports `Validation failed: Invalid checksum on recipient address` despite the Tx using a valid `to` address.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Run `clef` (I'm using HTTP)\r\n2. POST the following to clef.\r\n```\r\n[{\r\n  \"id\": 1,\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"method\": \"account_signTransaction\",\r\n  \"params\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"from\": \"0xf215e98b4f0c749fe9b78d0d4fa97ac7c9a4fe11\",\r\n      \"to\": \"0x07a565b7ed7d7a678680a4c162885bedbb695fe0\",\r\n      \"value\": \"0x1\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}]\r\n```\r\n3. See result:\r\n```\r\n[\r\n    {\r\n        \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n        \"id\": 1,\r\n        \"error\": {\r\n            \"code\": -32000,\r\n            \"message\": \"Validation failed: Invalid checksum on recipient address\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThis patch:\r\n```\r\ndiff --git a/signer/fourbyte/validation.go b/signer/fourbyte/validation.go\r\nindex 4d042d240..7c5bfb6e5 100644\r\n--- a/signer/fourbyte/validation.go\r\n+++ b/signer/fourbyte/validation.go\r\n@@ -68,7 +68,7 @@ func (db *Database) ValidateTransaction(selector *string, tx *core.SendTxArgs) (\r\n        }\r\n        // Not a contract creation, validate as a plain transaction\r\n        if !tx.To.ValidChecksum() {\r\n-               messages.Warn(\"Invalid checksum on recipient address\")\r\n+               messages.Warn(\"Invalid checksum on recipient address: \" + tx.To.String() + \"a: \" + tx.To.Address().Hex() + \" o: \" + tx.To.Original())\r\n        }\r\n        if bytes.Equal(tx.To.Address().Bytes(), common.Address{}.Bytes()) {\r\n                messages.Crit(\"Transaction recipient is the zero address\")\r\n```\r\nshows that `!tx.To.ValidChecksum()` is returning false because `original` and `Address` fields are not held in equivalent cases. https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/49b86a28590917eebf43bce213a2e0586db58755/common/types.go#L363\r\n\r\nThis can be resolved with the following patch:\r\n```\r\ndiff --git a/common/types.go b/common/types.go\r\nindex 8ca51a05f..93f049069 100644\r\n--- a/common/types.go\r\n+++ b/common/types.go\r\n@@ -360,7 +360,7 @@ func (ma *MixedcaseAddress) String() string {\r\n \r\n // ValidChecksum returns true if the address has valid checksum\r\n func (ma *MixedcaseAddress) ValidChecksum() bool {\r\n-       return ma.original == ma.addr.Hex()\r\n+       return strings.ToLower(ma.original) == strings.ToLower(ma.addr.Hex())\r\n }\r\n \r\n // Original returns the mixed-case input string\r\n``` \r\n\r\n... although I have a feeling that might not be addressing (get it?) the root cause of the issue...\r\n\r\n",
