    "body": "> And, perhaps also interestingly, it seems clef isn't validating the checksum of the from account address, just to.\r\n\r\nThere's no point checking the checksum on the `from` -- either you have the address and can do the signing, or you don't. So a mistyped address will simply fail. Whereas on the `to` part, a mistyped address can cause loss of funds.  ",
