    "created_at": "2020-06-04T09:04:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-06-04T09:04:46Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": ">  (Why checksum-validate one field and not the other?)\r\n\r\nChecksumming `to` prevents accidentally sending to a wrong recipient (funds lost forever)\r\nChecksumming 'from' prevenst accidentally trying to send from an address you do not control -- which will fail anyway. \r\n\r\n >  Is there anything to lose by validating checksums for all address fields just for the sake of consistency?\r\n\r\nYes, why add more errors for the user to run into when it's not needed? \r\n\r\n> do you want to spin the issue above about missing warnings off into it's own Issue?\r\n\r\nI don't see what the issue is around missing warnings...? \r\n\r\n> do you want to spin the issue above about the wiki documentation being wrong into it's own Issue?\r\n\r\nSGTM, thanks",
